Arab Polvara Resumes Operations After Strike Ends, Mal Says

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-10-16T08:26:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/arab-polvara-resumes-operations-after-strike-ends-mal-says.html
Arab Polvara Spinning & Weaving Co. (APSW) 
factories resumed operations at the end of last week after
workers ended a five-day strike,  Al Mal  newspaper reported,
citing Chairman Ayman Ismail.  The strike ended after the company agreed to raise pay in
accordance with increases due to be implemented at state-owned
textile companies, the Cairo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  